<div id="comment_65064365" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_65064365" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a rel="nofollow" id="comment_link_65064365" name="comment_link_65064365" href="//developers.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23569721&amp;cid=65064365" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(65064365)" >Low-level first</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_65064365" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 65064365); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>3</a>)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~stanjo74">stanjo74</a>  <span class="uid"><a rel="nofollow" href="//slashdot.org/~stanjo74">( 922718 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_65064365">		
		on Sunday January 05, 2025 @02:55PM (<span class="ind"></span><a rel="nofollow" href="//developers.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23569721&amp;cid=65064365">#65064365</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65064365"><p>Knowing low-level stuff first makes it much easier to understand high-level concepts  otherwise everything turns into rote memorization and cargo-cult.</p><p>Start with C (without the oddities) and computer architecture. Throw in some assembly to bridge the understanding between comp arch and C.<br>Then learn higher level abstractions through an imperative and a functional language. A "computer languages" course helps to bridge the syntactic sugar/high-level abstractions with low-level C.</p><p>The rest is operating systems, networks, advanced algorithms and data structures.</p></div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_65064365">
<span class="ind"></span><a id="reply_link_65064365" class="btn link" href="//developers.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23569721&amp;op=Reply&amp;threshold=1&amp;commentsort=0&amp;mode=thread&amp;pid=65064365" onclick="D2.replyTo(65064365); return false;">Reply to This</a> 	<a rel="nofollow" href="#" class="comment_share_toggle btn link">Share</a>
